At the water's edge,
  a soft breeze whispers secrets—
  tales of faraway.
  
  The waves lap gently,
  embracing both sand and stone,
  woven memories.
  
  I seek solace here,
  in the ebb and flow of tides—
  nature's heartbeat strong.

- Ishikawa Takuboku
